STATE OF MONTANA, Plaintiff, vs. JEFFREY SEITZINGER, Defendant, No. DC-01-245

Nunc Pro Tunc Order to Correct Decision

*25DATED this 30th day of March, 2006.

The first paragraph of the March 7,2006 Decision of the Sentence Review Division states the following: “On July 27,2005, the defendant was sentenced to five (5) years in the Montana State Prison for violation of the conditions of a suspended sentence for the offense of Aggravated Assault, a felony”.

The charge should be changed as contained in the September 10, 2001 Amended Information, namely the crime of ASSAULT ON A MINOR, a felony.

NOW, THEREFORE, IT IS ORDERED that the first paragraph of the Decision of the Sentence Review Division dated March 7, 2006, SHALL READ as follows:

On July 27, 2005, the defendant was sentenced to five (5) years in the Montana State Prison for violation of the conditions of a suspended sentence for the offense of Assault on a Minor, a felony.

Chairperson, Hon. John W. Whelan.
